							With its Loulo-Gounkoto gold mining complex continuing to grow production, Randgold Resources is looking at the development of a third underground mine there while at the same time expanding its footprint elsewhere in the region, chief executive Mark Bristow said here today.				
						
		


Read More











A LA RECHERCHE DE PLUS D’OPPORTUNITES AU MALI

02 February 2015


							Avec la croissance de la production de son complexe minier Loulo-Gounkoto, Randgold Resources explore la possibilité de développer une 3eme mine souterraine dans le même complexe tout en étendant son emprunt dans d’autres parties de la région, a dit Mark Bristow aujourd’hui.				
						
		


Read More











UN FILM DE SENSIBILISATION SUR EBOLA EN PREMIÈRE AU MALI

31 January 2015


							Un film produit par la société aurifère africaine Randgold Resources sur les mesures que les gens doivent observer pour ne pas contracter le virus Ebola a été projeté en première ce jour à l’hôtel Salam de Bamako.				
						
		


Read More











EBOLA AWARENESS FILM PREMIERED IN MALI

31 January 2015


							A film on the measures people should take to avoid contracting the Ebola virus, locally produced and sponsored by African gold miner Randgold Resources, was premiered today at the five-star Hotel Salam in Bamako.				
						
		


Read More











Treat all stakeholders as equals, says Randgold CEO

03 December 2014


							Gold mining companies should not prefer one stakeholder class over another but should ensure that all benefit equitably from their activities, Randgold Resources chief executive Mark Bristow said here today.				
						
		


